            <title>[SPARK-6975] Argument checking conflict in Yarn when dynamic allocation is enabled</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6975</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When dynamic allocation is enabled in yarn with default parameter, &lt;tt&gt;numExecutors&lt;/tt&gt; will be set to 0, but this will be failed in the following &lt;tt&gt;valideArgs()&lt;/tt&gt;, here &lt;tt&gt;numExecutors&lt;/tt&gt; must &amp;gt; 0, but for dynamic allocation, this executor number can be 0 (with default setting). The exception is shown as below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: You must specify at least 1 executor!&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
